description: Expansion of zeta function of icosian ring.
comments: Let zetaI(s) be the zeta function of icosian ring: zetaI(s)=zetaQ(tau)(2s)*zetaQ(tau)(2s-1) where zetaQ(tau)(s) is defined in A035187; then zetaI(s) = sum(n>=1,a(n)/A031363(n)^(2s)).Nonzero terms of A078473. - _Michel Marcus_, Mar 03 2014
links: M. Baake and R. V. Moody, Similarity submodules and root systems in four dimensions, Canad. J. Math. (1999), 51 1258-1276.
M. Baake and R. V. Moody, Similarity submodules and root systems in four dimensions, arXiv:math/9904028 [math.MG].
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
